    <string name="tutorial_step_progress">%1$d / %2$d</string>
    <string name="tutorial_step_intro_title">Meet your companion</string>
    <string name="tutorial_step_intro_body">This is your overlay companion — she floats over other apps so you can chat any time. The next few screens teach her gestures; you can try each one live.</string>
    <string name="tutorial_step_tap_title">Tap to walk</string>
    <string name="tutorial_step_tap_body">Tap her — she\'ll stroll across the screen. Give it a go.</string>
    <string name="tutorial_step_escape_title">Pester her to escape</string>
    <string name="tutorial_step_escape_body">Keep tapping and she gets startled, bolting off one edge and back in from the other. Pester her until she escapes.</string>
    <string name="tutorial_step_talk_title">Long-press to talk</string>
    <string name="tutorial_step_talk_body">Long-press her upper body to start a conversation — just speak and she\'ll answer aloud. If capture is on (set it in the quick menu), she also grabs your screen or snaps a photo so you can ask about what you see.</string>
    <string name="tutorial_step_recall_title">Long-press: recall</string>
    <string name="tutorial_step_recall_body">Missed what she said? Long-press her lower body to pop open her last reply. You can dismiss it, or type a follow-up right there.</string>
    <string name="tutorial_step_radial_title">Swipe up: quick menu</string>
    <string name="tutorial_step_radial_body">Swipe up to open the quick-settings dial. You can toggle capture mode, the volume-button shortcut, and Gemini vs on-device voice. Swipe down (or tap away) to close.</string>
    <string name="tutorial_step_visibility_title">Hide &amp; show</string>
    <string name="tutorial_step_visibility_body">Double-press Volume Down to hide her; double-press again to bring her back.</string>
    <string name="tutorial_step_voice_title">Hands-free listening</string>
    <string name="tutorial_step_voice_body">Triple-press Volume Down or press an assistant button to start listening — no screen tap needed. She transcribes, thinks, and answers aloud. Tap her to replay.</string>
    <string name="tutorial_step_tools_title">Web search &amp; tools</string>
    <string name="tutorial_step_tools_body">Ask about current events and she\'ll search the web. If you\'ve connected tool servers (MCP), she can call those too — watch for the 🔧 badge. Tap her to replay.</string>
    <string name="tutorial_step_ghost_title">Ghost mode</string>
    <string name="tutorial_step_ghost_body">When a keyboard appears she turns semi-transparent and lets taps pass through, so she never blocks what you\'re typing.</string>
    <string name="tutorial_step_outro_title">You\'re all set</string>
    <string name="tutorial_step_outro_body">That\'s the tour. Tap to walk, long-press to talk or recall, swipe up for quick settings. Have fun!</string>
    <string name="tutorial_recall_placeholder">This is where my last reply would appear!</string>
    <string name="tutorial_canned_response">Ooh, a code editor~ Looks like you\'re deep in a Kotlin file. Want me to explain what\'s on screen, or just keep you company?</string>
    <string name="tutorial_canned_followup">Got it! That\'s exactly how a real reply works — I\'d read it and answer. Try the next gesture when you\'re ready. ✨</string>
    <string name="tutorial_canned_voice_reply">You said that out loud and I heard you~ This very reply is my on-device voice — no internet required. Handy when you\'d rather talk than type.</string>
    <string name="tutorial_canned_search_reply">It\'s sunny and 72 degrees~ That came from a weather tool. In the real app I can call tools and search the web for you.</string>

